flavor_text_entries.ruby:
Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,”
SHARPEDO is widely feared.
Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off.
Just one of these POKéMON can
thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.
flavor_text_entries.sapphire:
SHARPEDO can swim at speeds of up to
75 mph by jetting seawater out of its
backside. This POKéMON’s drawback is its inability
to swim long distances.
flavor_text_entries.emerald:
The vicious and sly gangster of the sea.
Its skin is specially textured to minimize
drag in water. Its speed tops out at over
75 miles per hour.
flavor_text_entries.firered:
The ruffian of the seas, it has fangs that
crunch through iron. It swims by jetting
water from its rear.

flavor_text_entries.omega-ruby:
Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,” Sharpedo is widely feared.
Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one
of these Pokémon can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.
flavor_text_entries.alpha-sapphire:
Sharpedo can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting
seawater out of its backside. This Pokémon’s drawback is its
inability to swim long distances.
flavor_text_entries.sun:
It pursues its prey at speeds of 75 mph and
finishes them off with fangs that can crush iron.
It is known as the bully of the sea.
flavor_text_entries.moon:
It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin
was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokémon
became a victim of overfishing.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
People believe that carrying one of its
discarded fangs will prevent mishaps at sea,
so the fangs are made into accessories.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
It drinks in seawater and jets it from its rear to
propel itself. It’s very sensitive to the scent
of blood.
flavor_text_entries.sword:
As soon as it catches the scent of prey, Sharpedo
will jet seawater from its backside, hurtling
toward the target to attack at 75 mph.
flavor_text_entries.shield:
This Pokémon is known as the Bully of the Sea.
Any ship entering the waters Sharpedo calls
home will be attacked—no exceptions.
